Step 1

Go to Profile--> settings-->ssh keys
copy the ssh public key and save it (locations /root/.ssh/)

Step 2
Download your repositary to your directory
Goto repository -->code-->copy the URL

Step 3
Go to your directory
git clone (paste your URL here)

How to update your git repo from server
1. git add file name (if you add any new file)
2. git commit -m "your Comment"
3. git push or git push orgin master

How to update your directory from GIT Repo
git pull

How to update the git username and email

1. git config --global user.name "hasitha"
2. git config --global user.email "rugbyhasi@gmai.com"

